        "title": "Long Range Ultrasonic Testing (LRUT)",
        "content1": {
            "title": "Long Range Ultrasonic Testing – NDT Inspection Technique",
            "subtitle": "Long Range Ultrasonic Testing is an advanced technology for detecting and analysing corrosion where access is difficult."
        },
        "content2": {
            "title": "Benefits",
            "subtitle": [{
                    "text": "Low cost screening with 100% coverage"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Focussing capability to evaluate corrosion distribution around pipe circumference"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Typical test range 60m from single location, ideal conditions can achieve longer distance."
                },
                {
                    "text": "Testing of pipes up to 48” diameter"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Proven capability on pipe in service up to 125 oC"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Detection of metal loss > 3%"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Ideal where conventional testing is impossible or very costly e.g. clamped,insulated, elevated, sleeved or buried pipes."
                }
            ]
        },
        "content3": {
            "title": "Process",
            "subtitle": [{
                    "text": "Low frequency ultrasound is transmitted and received from a single location"
                },
                {
                    "text": "The guided waves used travel long distances, even in buried, submerged or insulated pipe"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Reponse from flaws is a function of their depth and circumferential extent"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Focussing allows ultrasound energy to be concentrated into a small region of pipe for detailed localised inspection"
                },
                {
                    "text": "Teletest® uses ‘multi-mode’ technology to characterise and quantify any flaw detected"
                },
                {
                    "text": "A laptop PC runs dedicated Teletest® data acquisition and analysis software. The flaw detector communicates with the PC via a high-speed data link"
                }
            ]
        },
